# 13
msgid "Summarizing core ideas... about how animals respond"
msgstr ""
"Resumiendo las ideas fundamentales... sobre cómo responden los animales"

msgid ""
"<span class='key'>Neurons</span> (<span class='key'>nervous system cells</"
"span>) are organized into networks known as the <span class='key'>central</"
"span> and <span class='key'>peripheral</span> nervous systems. The central "
"nervous system is the brain and spinal cord. The peripheral nervous system "
"is all of the many nerve cells throughout the body that connect to the "
"spinal cord. The cells of the peripheral nervous system are divided into "
"<span class='key'>sensory</span> and <span class='key'>motor</span> neurons. "
"The nervous system is sensitive to three different types of <span "
"class='key'>stimuli</span>: <span class='key'>mechanical</span>, <span "
"class='key'>chemical</span>, and <span class='key'>electromagnetic</span> "
"stimuli. A <span class='key'>receptor</span> is a nerve cell that is "
"sensitive to chemical stimuli based on shape. Special touch receptors in the "
"ear transmit the pattern of vibration to the brain as an electrical signal. "
"The brain interprets the pattern as sound. Smell and taste are both the "
"result of chemical stimulation. Humans perceive taste thanks to structures "
"on our tongues called <span class='key'>taste buds</span>. Smell receptors "
"work much like taste receptors, but are concentrated in the nose, and work "
"for molecules suspended in the air. Our eyes contain four types of light-"
"sensitive sensory neurons. Located in the <span class='key'>retina</span>, "
"they respond to different types of light. <span class='key'>Rods</span> are "
"neurons that sense brightness. The ability to see a clear image depends on "
"having the proper distance between the lens and retina called the focal "
"length. <span class='key'>Memory</span> patterns form when cells communicate "
"with one another. One nerve cell sends a message to another by releasing "
"chemicals into the space between called the <span class='key'>synapse</"
"span>. When this communication happens a few times, a temporary pattern "
"known as <span class='key'>short-term memory</span> is formed. <span "
"class='key'>Chunking</span>, <span class='key'>imagery</span>, and <span "
"class='key'>practice</span> is how one's memory can be improved. These tools "
"work by strengthening the connections between cells in the brain."
msgstr ""
"<span class='key'>Las neuronas </span>(<span class='key'>células del sistema "
"nervioso</span> ) están organizados en redes conocidas como<span "
"class='key'> los sistemas nerviosos centrales </span>y <span "
"class='key'>periféricos</span>. El sistema nervioso central es el cerebro y "
"la médula espinal. El sistema nervioso periférico es las muchas células "
"nerviosas en todo el cuerpo que se conectan a la médula espinal. Las células "
"del sistema nervioso periférico se dividen en<span class='key'> las neuronas "
"sensoriales</span> y motoras</span>. El sistema nervioso es sensible a tres "
"tipos diferentes de <span class='key'>estímulos</span> : <span "
"class='key'>mecánicos</span> , <span class='key'>químicos</span> y estímulos "
"<span class='key'>electromagnéticos</span>. Un<span class='key'> receptor </"
"span> es una célula nerviosa que es sensible a estímulos químicos basada en "
"la forma. Los receptores táctiles especiales en el oído transmiten el patrón "
"de vibraciones al cerebro como una señal eléctrica. El cerebro interpreta el "
"patrón como sonido. El olfato y el gusto son el resultado de la estimulación "
"química.   Los seres humanos perciben el gusto gracias a las estructuras en "
"nuestras lenguas llamadas <span class='key'>papilas gustativas</span>. Los "
"receptores del olfato funcionan como receptores de sabor , pero se "
"concentran en la nariz, y funcionan para las moléculas suspendidas en el "
"aire. Nuestros ojos contienen cuatro tipos de neuronas sensoriales sensibles "
"a la luz. Situadas en la <span class='key'>retina</span>,  responden a "
"diferentes tipos de luz. <span class='key'>Las varillas</span> son las "
"neuronas que detectan el brillo. La capacidad de ver una imagen clara "
"depende de tener la distancia adecuada entre el cristalino y la retina "
"llamada la longitud focal. <span class='key'>Los patrones de memoria </"
"span>se forman cuando las células se comunican entre sí. Una célula nerviosa "
"envía un mensaje a otro por la liberación de sustancias químicas en el "
"espacio entre ellas llamado <span class='key'>sinapsis</span>. Cuando esta "
"comunicación ocurre un par de veces , se forma un patrón temporal conocido "
"como <span class='key'>la memoria a corto plazo</span>. <span class='key'>En "
"trozos</span> ,<span class='key'> imágenes</span>, y <span class='key'> la "
"práctica</span> es la forma en que la memoria de uno puede ser mejorado. "
"Estas herramientas funcionan mediante el fortalecimiento de las conexiones "
"entre las células en el cerebro."

